{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839680670,"sessionID":"ses_287b5421cffepKtWCnuNTsxy0u","part":{"id":"prt_d784b0dd9001soKokL0N5eZa1F","messageID":"msg_d784af8b2001UHp7WzuLNJqQa1","sessionID":"ses_287b5421cffepKtWCnuNTsxy0u","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_3212eab31d1a4f36b004a634","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-001 â€” CRD AgentRuntime ç±»ĺž‹ĺ®šäą‰ Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/apis  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design completed)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Scaffold & Registration\n11: \n12: - [ ] **1.1** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` directory structure\n13: - [ ] **1.2** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/register.go` - register API group\n14: - [ ] **1.3** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` - define `SchemeGroupVersion`, `SchemeBuilder`, `AddToScheme`\n15: - [ ] **1.4** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` - add Go package documentation\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## Phase 2: Type Definitions\n20: \n21: - [ ] **2.1** Define `AgentRuntimePhase` enum (Pending, Running, Failed, Terminating)\n22: - [ ] **2.2** Define `AgentRuntimeCondition` struct (type, status, reason, message, lastTransitionTime)\n23: - [ ] **2.3** Define `CodeInterpreterSpec` struct (enabled, image, resources)\n24: - [ ] **2.4** Define `ResourceQuota` struct (cpu, memory, storage limits)\n25: - [ ] **2.5** Define `NetworkPolicy` struct (egressRules, ingressRules)\n26: - [ ] **2.6** Define `LifecycleHook` struct (preStart, postStop handlers)\n27: - [ ] **2.7** Define `AgentRuntimeSpec` struct (container, resources, network, lifecycle, codeInterpreter)\n28: - [ ] **2.8** Define `AgentRuntimeStatus` struct (phase, conditions, sandboxRef, startTime, lastTransitionTime)\n29: - [ ] **2.9** Define `AgentRuntime` struct (TypeMeta, ObjectMeta, Spec, Status)\n30: - [ ] **2.10** Define `AgentRuntimeList` struct (TypeMeta, ListMeta, Items)\n31: - [ ] **2.11** Add JSON tags (camelCase) and protobuf tags to all types\n32: - [ ] **2.12** Implement `runtime.Object` interface for AgentRuntime and AgentRuntimeList\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ## Phase 3: Defaults & Validation\n37: \n38: - [ ] **3.1** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/defaults.go`\n39: - [ ] **3.2** Implement `SetDefaults_AgentRuntime` - set default phase to Pending, default resources if unspecified\n40: - [ ] **3.3** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation.go`\n41: - [ ] **3.4** Implement `ValidateAgentRuntime` - validate spec fields (resource values, image format, hook URLs)\n42: - [ ] **3.5** Implement `ValidateAgentRuntimeStatusUpdate` - validate status transitions and field immutability\n43: \n44: ---\n45: \n46: ## Phase 4: CRD Manifest Generation\n47: \n48: - [ ] **4.1** Add `+genclient` and `+k8s:deepcopy-gen` markers to type definitions\n49: - [ ] **4.2** Add `+kubebuilder:object:root=true` and `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` markers\n50: - [ ] **4.3** Add `+kubebuilder:printcolumn` markers for kubectl output (NAME, PHASE, SANDBOX, AGE)\n51: - [ ] **4.4** Run `make gen-crd` (controller-gen) to generate CRD YAML\n52: - [ ] **4.5** Verify generated manifest at `manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml`\n53: - [ ] **4.6** Validate OpenAPI v3 schema in generated CRD\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## Phase 5: Client Code Generation\n58: \n59: - [ ] **5.1** Update `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` if needed\n60: - [ ] **5.2** Update `hack/update-codegen.sh` with API group info\n61: - [ ] **5.3** Run `make gen-client` to generate clientset, listers, informers\n62: - [ ] **5.4** Verify generated code compiles: `pkg/client/clientset/versioned/`\n63: - [ ] **5.5** Verify generated code compiles: `pkg/client/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n64: - [ ] **5.6** Verify generated code compiles: `pkg/client/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ## Phase 6: Unit Tests\n69: \n70: - [ ] **6.1** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types_test.go`\n71: - [ ] **6.2** Test type round-trip serialization (Go â†’ JSON â†’ Go)\n72: - [ ] **6.3** Test `SetDefaults_AgentRuntime` behavior\n73: - [ ] **6.4** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation_test.go`\n74: - [ ] **6.5** Test valid AgentRuntime specs pass validation\n75: - [ ] **6.6** Test invalid specs fail validation (negative resources, invalid image names)\n76: - [ ] **6.7** Test status update validation (phase transitions, immutable fields)\n77: - [ ] **6.8** Test `AddToScheme` registration works correctly\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## Phase 7: Integration & Verification\n82: \n83: - [ ] **7.1** Run `make test` - all unit tests pass\n84: - [ ] **7.2** Run `make verify` - code generation is up to date\n85: - [ ] **7.3** Apply CRD to test cluster: `kubectl apply -f manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml`\n86: - [ ] **7.4** Verify `kubectl get agentruntime` shows custom columns\n87: - [ ] **7.5** Create sample AgentRuntime YAML in `examples/agentruntime.yaml`\n88: - [ ] **7.6** Apply sample and verify resource is created\n89: - [ ] **7.7** Verify Go client can create/get/update AgentRuntime resources\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## Verification Checklist\n94: \n95: - [ ] All Go code compiles without errors\n96: - [ ] `go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/...` passes with â‰Ą80% coverage\n97: - [ ] CRD manifest validates with `kubeval` or `kubectl --dry-run=server`\n98: - [ ] Generated client code is up to date (`git diff` shows no changes after `make gen-client`)\n99: - [ ] Example YAML applies successfully to test cluster\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## Dependencies\n104: \n105: | Task | Depends On |\n106: |------|------------|\n107: | Phase 2 | Phase 1 |\n108: | Phase 3 | Phase 2 |\n109: | Phase 4 | Phase 2 |\n110: | Phase 5 | Phase 4 |\n111: | Phase 6 | Phase 2, 3 |\n112: | Phase 7 | Phase 4, 5, 6 |\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ## References\n117: \n118: - Proposal: `changes/AR-001/proposal.md`\n119: - Implementation Plan: `proposal.md#implementation-plan`\n120: - Success Criteria: `proposal.md#success-criteria`\n121: - API Conventions: `https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md`\n\n(End of file - total 121 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-001 â€” CRD AgentRuntime ç±»ĺž‹ĺ®šäą‰ Tasks\n\n**Module:** pkg/apis  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Scaffold & Registration\n\n- [ ] **1.1** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` directory structure\n- [ ] **1.2** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/register.go` - register API group\n- [ ] **1.3** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` - define `SchemeGroupVersion`, `SchemeBuilder`, `AddToScheme`\n- [ ] **1.4** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` - add Go package documentation\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Type Definitions\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775839680645,"end":1775839680669}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839680673,"sessionID":"ses_287b5421cffepKtWCnuNTsxy0u","part":{"id":"prt_d784b13780016SQXD9Y58ighET","messageID":"msg_d784af8b2001UHp7WzuLNJqQa1","sessionID":"ses_287b5421cffepKtWCnuNTsxy0u","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_8b0feb6212b049319d3f84f5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-001 â€” CRD AgentRuntime ç±»ĺž‹ĺ®šäą‰\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) and associated types for the AgentCube platform. This CRD enables users to declare and manage AI agent runtime configurations as Kubernetes-native resources, providing the foundation for sandbox orchestration and lifecycle management.\n6: \n7: The `AgentRuntime` resource represents a configurable agent execution environment with support for:\n8: - Code interpreter attachment\n9: - Resource quotas (CPU, memory, storage)\n10: - Network policies and egress rules\n11: - Lifecycle hooks (preStart, postStop)\n12: - Status tracking (phase, conditions, sandbox reference)\n13: \n14: ## Scope\n15: \n16: **Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n17: **API Group:** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`  \n18: **Kind:** `AgentRuntime` (namespaced)  \n19: **Size:** S\n20: \n21: ### In Scope\n22: \n23: 1. **Type Definitions** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`)\n24:    - `AgentRuntime` - main resource struct\n25:    - `AgentRuntimeSpec` - desired state specification\n26:    - `AgentRuntimeStatus` - observed state status\n27:    - `CodeInterpreterSpec` - embedded code interpreter configuration\n28:    - `ResourceQuota` - sandbox resource limits\n29:    - `NetworkPolicy` - egress/ingress rules\n30:    - `LifecycleHook` - preStart/postStop callbacks\n31:    - `AgentRuntimePhase` - lifecycle phase enum\n32:    - `AgentRuntimeCondition` - status conditions\n33: \n34: 2. **API Registration** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go`)\n35:    - `SchemeGroupVersion` definition\n36:    - `SchemeBuilder` registration\n37:    - `AddToScheme` function\n38:    - `Resource` and `Kind` helpers\n39: \n40: 3. **CRD Manifest** (`manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml`)\n41:    - OpenAPI v3 schema validation\n42:    - Subresources: `/status`, `/scale` (if needed)\n43:    - AdditionalPrinterColumns for kubectl output\n44:    - Conversion webhook placeholders (future)\n45: \n46: 4. **Defaulting & Validation** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/defaults.go`, `validation.go`)\n47:    - `SetDefaults_AgentRuntime` - default values\n48:    - `ValidateAgentRuntime` - spec validation rules\n49:    - `ValidateAgentRuntimeStatusUpdate` - status update validation\n50: \n51: 5. **Utility Functions**\n52:    - Phase transition helpers\n53:    - Condition management (GetCondition, SetCondition, RemoveCondition)\n54:    - Deep copy utilities (via code generation)\n55: \n56: ### Out of Scope\n57: \n58: - Controller implementation (covered by AR-002)\n59: - Webhook admission controllers (deferred to AR-010)\n60: - Conversion webhooks for version upgrades (deferred)\n61: - CLI commands for AgentRuntime (Python SDK task)\n62: \n63: ## Impact Analysis\n64: \n65: ### Dependencies\n66: \n67: | Dependency | Type | Reason |\n68: |------------|------|--------|\n69: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Required | MetaV1 types, runtime.Object, schema |\n70: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Required | ResourceList, PodSecurityContext, EnvVar |\n71: | `k8s.io/client-go` | Generated | Clientset, listers, informers (via `make gen-client`) |\n72: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis` | Module | API group registration |\n73: \n74: ### Downstream Consumers\n75: \n76: 1. **Controller (AR-002)**: Watches `AgentRuntime` resources, reconciles to create sandbox pods\n77: 2. **Router**: Reads `AgentRuntime` status to route traffic to active sandboxes\n78: 3. **Python SDK**: Provides high-level API for creating/managing AgentRuntime resources\n79: 4. **CLI Tool**: Exposes `agentcube runtime create/get/list/delete` commands\n80: 5. **Helm Chart**: Ships CRD manifest for cluster installation\n81: \n82: ### Breaking Changes\n83: \n84: None - this is the initial definition of the API.\n85: \n86: ### Migration Path\n87: \n88: Not applicable for initial implementation. Future version migrations (v1alpha2, v1beta1) will require:\n89: - Conversion webhook implementation\n90: - Storage version bumps\n91: - helm chart upgrade hooks\n92: \n93: ## Alternatives Considered\n94: \n95: ### Alternative 1: Use Deployment + ConfigMap instead of CRD\n96: \n97: **Approach:** Represent agent runtimes as standard Kubernetes Deployments with configuration in ConfigMaps.\n98: \n99: **Pros:**\n100: - No CRD complexity or controller required\n101: - Leverages built-in Kubernetes primitives\n102: - Simpler RBAC story\n103: \n104: **Cons:**\n105: - Loses semantic meaning (Deployment is generic)\n106: - Complex validation logic in admission webhooks\n107: - Status reporting requires custom annotations\n108: - Harder to query/filter agent-specific resources\n109: - No custom subresources (e.g., `/exec`, `/logs` future extensions)\n110: \n111: **Decision:** Rejected. CRD provides better abstraction, type safety, and extensibility for AgentCube semantics.\n112: \n113: ### Alternative 2: Single monolithic AgentRuntime CRD with all features\n114: \n115: **Approach:** Include all possible configuration options (networking, storage, auth, scheduling) in one large spec.\n116: \n117: **Pros:**\n118: - One resource to rule them all\n119: - Maximum flexibility for users\n120: \n121: **Cons:**\n122: - High cognitive load for simple use cases\n123: - Validation complexity\n124: - Harder to evolve individual aspects\n125: - Violates separation of concerns\n126: \n127: **Decision:** Rejected. Prefer composable design with `CodeInterpreter` as separate but related resource. Core `AgentRuntime` focuses on execution environment; advanced features (distributed training, multi-agent orchestration) can be future extensions.\n128: \n129: ### Alternative 3: Use Pod-level primitives (PodTemplate) directly\n130: \n131: **Approach:** Embed raw PodTemplateSpec in AgentRuntime spec.\n132: \n133: **Pros:**\n134: - Full Kubernetes pod configuration available\n135: - No translation layer needed\n136: \n137: **Cons:**\n138: - Exposes low-level K8s details to end users\n139: - Harder to enforce platform policies\n140: - Breaks abstraction if K8s pod spec changes\n141: \n142: **Decision:** Partially adopted. AgentRuntimeSpec contains a simplified `Container` subset (image, env, resources) rather than full PodSpec, with controller translating to Pod internals. This balances flexibility with abstraction.\n143: \n144: ## Implementation Plan\n145: \n146: 1. **Scaffold directory structure**\n147:    - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n148:    - `pkg/apis/runtime/register.go` (group registration)\n149: \n150: 2. **Define Go types** (`types.go`)\n151:    - Core structs with JSON tags\n152:    - Phase enum and conditions\n153:    - Embedded CodeInterpreterSpec\n154: \n155: 3. **Implement registration** (`register.go`)\n156:    - SchemeGroupVersion constants\n157:    - SchemeBuilder wiring\n158: \n159: 4. **Add defaults and validation**\n160:    - `defaults.go`: SetDefaults_AgentRuntime\n161:    - `validation.go`: ValidateAgentRuntime\n162: \n163: 5. **Generate CRD manifest**\n164:    - Run `make gen-crd` (controller-gen)\n165:    - Place in `manifests/charts/base/crds/`\n166: \n167: 6. **Generate client code**\n168:    - Run `make gen-client` (code-generator)\n169:    - Produces clientset, listers, informers\n170: \n171: 7. **Write unit tests**\n172:    - Type round-trip serialization\n173:    - Defaulting behavior\n174:    - Validation rules\n175: \n176: ## Success Criteria\n177: \n178: - [ ] `AgentRuntime` CRD installs via Helm chart\n179: - [ ] `kubectl apply -f agentruntime.yaml` succeeds\n180: - [ ] `kubectl get agentruntime` shows custom columns\n181: - [ ] Go client can create/get/update AgentRuntime\n182: - [ ] Spec validation rejects invalid resources\n183: - [ ] Defaulting applies expected values\n184: - [ ] Code generation produces compilable client-go code\n185: \n186: ## References\n187: \n188: - [Kubernetes API Conventions](https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md)\n189: - [Controller Tools CRD Generation](https://book.kubebuilder.io/reference/markers/crd.html)\n190: - [Kubernetes Code Generator](https://github.com/kubernetes/code-generator)\n191: - AgentCube deployment spec: `deployment/spec.md`\n192: - Client-go reference: `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n(End of file - total 192 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-001 â€” CRD AgentRuntime ç±»ĺž‹ĺ®šäą‰\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) and associated types for the AgentCube platform. This CRD enables users to declare and manage AI agent runtime configurations as Kubernetes-native resources, providing the foundation for sandbox orchestration and lifecycle management.\n\nThe `AgentRuntime` resource represents a configurable agent execution environment with support for:\n- Code interpreter attachment\n- Resource quotas (CPU, memory, storage)\n- Network policies and egress rules\n- Lifecycle hooks (preStart, postStop)\n- Status tracking (phase, conditions, sandbox reference)\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**API Group:** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`  \n**Kind:** `AgentRuntime` (namespaced)  \n**Size:** S\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775839680647,"end":1775839680671}}}}
