{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839761065,"sessionID":"ses_287b5421cffepKtWCnuNTsxy0u","part":{"id":"prt_d784bd427001n6dS1g8ovMnnoZ","messageID":"msg_d784bc56a001ht1Gs2u6AItIVr","sessionID":"ses_287b5421cffepKtWCnuNTsxy0u","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_ab50dc56a2d94a8088ecf95a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: AR-002 â€” CRD CodeInterpreter ç±»ĺž‹ĺ®šäą‰\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the `CodeInterpreter` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) and associated types for the AgentCube platform. This CRD enables users to declare and manage code interpreter configurations as Kubernetes-native resources, providing isolated kernel environments for AI agent code execution.\n\nThe `CodeInterpreter` resource represents a configurable code execution environment with support for:\n- Multiple kernel languages (Python, R, Julia, etc.)\n- Session management and lifecycle\n- Security policies (package allowlists, operation restrictions)\n- Resource quotas (CPU, memory per session)\n- Status tracking (phase, conditions, active sessions)\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**API Group:** `codeinterpreter.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`  \n**Kind:** `CodeInterpreter` (namespaced)  \n**Size:** S\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **Type Definitions** (`pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/types.go`)\n   - `CodeInterpreter` - main resource struct\n   - `CodeInterpreterSpec` - desired state specification\n   - `CodeInterpreterStatus` - observed state status\n   - `KernelSpec` - kernel configuration (language, image, resources)\n   - `SessionConfig` - session timeout and limits\n   - `SecurityPolicy` - package allowlists and operation restrictions\n   - `CodeInterpreterPhase` - lifecycle phase enum\n   - `CodeInterpreterCondition` - status conditions\n\n2. **API Registration** (`pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/register.go`)\n   - `SchemeGroupVersion` definition\n   - `SchemeBuilder` registration\n   - `AddToScheme` function\n   - `Resource` and `Kind` helpers\n\n3. **CRD Manifest** (`manifests/charts/base/crds/codeinterpreter.yaml`)\n   - OpenAPI v3 schema validation\n   - Subresources: `/status`\n   - AdditionalPrinterColumns for kubectl output\n   - Conversion webhook placeholders (future)\n\n4. **Defaulting & Validation** (`pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/defaults.go`, `validation.go`)\n   - `SetDefaults_CodeInterpreter` - default values\n   - `ValidateCodeInterpreter` - spec validation rules\n   - `ValidateCodeInterpreterStatusUpdate` - status update validation\n\n5. **Utility Functions**\n   - Phase transition helpers\n   - Condition management (GetCondition, SetCondition, RemoveCondition)\n   - Deep copy utilities (via code generation)\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Controller implementation (deferred to AR-003)\n- Kernel image building and management (infrastructure task)\n- Session WebSocket proxying (deferred to router component)\n- Python SDK bindings (Python SDK task)\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Type | Reason |\n|------------|------|--------|\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Required | MetaV1 types, runtime.Object, schema |\n| `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Required | ResourceList, SecurityContext, EnvVar |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | Generated | Clientset, listers, informers (via `make gen-client`) |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis` | Module | API group registration |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **Controller (AR-003)**: Watches `CodeInterpreter` resources, reconciles to create kernel pods\n2. **AgentRuntime (AR-001)**: References `CodeInterpreter` for agent code execution capability\n3. **Router**: Manages WebSocket connections to active interpreter sessions\n4. **Python SDK**: Provides high-level API for creating/managing CodeInterpreter resources\n5. **CLI Tool**: Exposes `agentcube interpreter create/get/list/delete` commands\n6. **Helm Chart**: Ships CRD manifest for cluster installation\n\n### Breaking Changes\n\nNone - this is the initial definition of the API.\n\n### Migration Path\n\nNot applicable for initial implementation. Future version migrations (v1alpha2, v1beta1) will require:\n- Conversion webhook implementation\n- Storage version bumps\n- Helm chart upgrade hooks\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Embed CodeInterpreter config in AgentRuntime\n\n**Approach:** Include code interpreter configuration as a nested field within `AgentRuntime` spec.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Single resource to manage\n- Simpler deployment model\n- No additional CRD overhead\n\n**Cons:**\n- Couples agent lifecycle with interpreter lifecycle\n- Cannot share interpreters across agents\n- Harder to scale interpreters independently\n- Limits multi-language support per agent\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. Separating concerns allows interpreters to be managed, scaled, and versioned independently. Multiple agents can reference the same interpreter, and agents can switch interpreters without recreation.\n\n### Alternative 2: Use Jupyter kernel gateway directly\n\n**Approach:** Deploy Jupyter Kernel Gateway as a standard Deployment and manage kernels via REST API.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Leverages existing Jupyter ecosystem\n- Mature kernel management\n- Built-in WebSocket support\n\n**Cons:**\n- No Kubernetes-native resource model\n- Custom integration required for lifecycle management\n- Harder to enforce cluster-wide policies\n- No status reporting to Kubernetes API\n\n**Decision:** Partially adopted. CodeInterpreter CRD represents the desired state; controller will create/manage Jupyter Kernel Gateway deployments based on CRD spec. This combines K8s-native abstraction with proven kernel technology.\n\n### Alternative 3: One CodeInterpreter per language\n\n**Approach:** Create separate CRDs for PythonInterpreter, RInterpreter, JuliaInterpreter, etc.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Language-specific validation rules\n- Clear separation of concerns\n- Simpler schemas per CRD\n\n**Cons:**\n- CRD proliferation\n- Duplicate code across CRDs\n- Harder to support polyglot agents\n- More complex client code\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. Single `CodeInterpreter` CRD with `KernelSpec.language` field provides flexibility while maintaining simplicity. Validation rules can branch on language field.\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n1. **Scaffold directory structure**\n   - `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/`\n   - `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/register.go` (group registration)\n\n2. **Define Go types** (`types.go`)\n   - Core structs with JSON tags\n   - Phase enum and conditions\n   - KernelSpec and SecurityPolicy\n\n3. **Implement registration** (`register.go`)\n   - SchemeGroupVersion constants\n   - SchemeBuilder wiring\n\n4. **Add defaults and validation**\n   - `defaults.go`: SetDefaults_CodeInterpreter\n   - `validation.go`: ValidateCodeInterpreter\n\n5. **Generate CRD manifest**\n   - Run `make gen-crd` (controller-gen)\n   - Place in `manifests/charts/base/crds/`\n\n6. **Generate client code**\n   - Run `make gen-client` (code-generator)\n   - Produces clientset, listers, informers\n\n7. **Write unit tests**\n   - Type round-trip serialization\n   - Defaulting behavior\n   - Validation rules\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] `CodeInterpreter` CRD installs via Helm chart\n- [ ] `kubectl apply -f codeinterpreter.yaml` succeeds\n- [ ] `kubectl get codeinterpreter` shows custom columns\n- [ ] Go client can create/get/update CodeInterpreter\n- [ ] Spec validation rejects invalid resources\n- [ ] Defaulting applies expected values\n- [ ] Code generation produces compilable client-go code\n\n## References\n\n- [Kubernetes API Conventions](https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md)\n- [Controller Tools CRD Generation](https://book.kubebuilder.io/reference/markers/crd.html)\n- [Kubernetes Code Generator](https://github.com/kubernetes/code-generator)\n- Jupyter Kernel Gateway: https://jupyter-kernel-gateway.readthedocs.io/\n- Related: `changes/AR-001/` (AgentRuntime CRD)\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775839761049,"end":1775839761060}}}}
